
Overview of adv constantly

The adv constantly has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) constantly, invariably, always -- (without variation or change, in every case; "constantly kind and gracious"; "he always arrives on time")
2. (1) constantly, always, forever, perpetually, incessantly -- (without interruption; "the world is constantly changing")
